<para id="fs-idm287020448">Before using this Primary Source, students should be familiar with the disputed election of 1824 and the Tariff of 1828 (called the Tariff of Abominations). This Primary Source should be accompanied by the <link class="target-chapter" document="m79368">Is the Concurrent Majority Theory Faithful to the Ideals of the Constitution?</link> Point-Counterpoint and the <link class="target-chapter" document="m79377">John C. Calhoun, “Slavery as a Positive Good,” 1837</link> Primary Source to highlight Calhoun’s impact on domestic politics during the Age of Jackson.</para>
